import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    avg_stock_price = data.groupby('symbol')['price'].mean()
    
    ax = avg_stock_price.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average stock price for each company?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    for company in data['symbol'].unique():
        company_data = data[data['symbol'] == company]
        plt.plot(company_data['date'], company_data['price'], label=company)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Stock Price')
    plt.title('What is the trend of stock prices over time for each company?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    companies = data['symbol'].unique()
    for company in companies:
        company_data = data[data['symbol'] == company]
        plt.hist(company_data['price'], alpha=0.5, label=company)
    
    plt.xlabel('Stock Prices')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Company')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of stock prices for each company?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    # Convert date fields to date types
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    
    # Scatter plot of stock prices between two companies
    company_symbols = data['symbol'].unique()
    for i, symbol in enumerate(company_symbols[:-1]):
        for symbol2 in company_symbols[i+1:]:
            company1_data = data[data['symbol'] == symbol]
            company2_data = data[data['symbol'] == symbol2]
            merged_data = company1_data.merge(company2_data, on='date', suffixes=('_1', '_2'))
            plt.scatter(merged_data['price_1'], merged_data['price_2'], label=f'{symbol} vs {symbol2}')
    
    plt.xlabel('Stock Price of Company 1')
    plt.ylabel('Stock Price of Company 2')
    plt.legend()
    
    # Rotate the x axis label if necessary
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the correlation between stock prices of different companies?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    box_plot = data.boxplot(column='price', by='symbol', grid=False)
    plt.title('What is the volatility of stock prices for each company?')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xlabel('Company')
    plt.ylabel('Stock Price')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        box_plot.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
